This directory contains scripts to produce topo files for CAM applications.

The naming convention is based on CAM "hgrid" identifier (which uses resolution specifications native to the dynamical core).

Uniform resolution grids
========================

CAM-EUL	   	      : 256x512      , 128x256.nc    , 64x128		, 48x96		, 32x64		, 8x16
CAM-FV 	 	      : 0.23x0.31    , 0.47x0.63     , 0.5x0.625	, 0.9x1.25	, 1.9x2.5 	, 2.5x3.33	, 4x5	, 10x15
CAM-FV3	 	      : C24	     , C48	     , C96		, C192		, C384
CAM-SE 	 	      : ne5np4	     , ne16np4	     , ne30np4		, ne60np4	, ne120np4	, ne240np4
CAM-SE-CSLAM	      : ne5pg2	     , ne16pg2	     , ne30pg2		, ne60pg2	, ne120pg2	, ne240pg2 
CAM-SE-CSLAM	      : ne5pg3	     , ne16pg3	     , ne30pg3		, ne60pg3	, ne120pg3	, ne240pg3
CAM-SE-CSLAM	      : ne5pg4	     , ne16pg4	     , ne30pg4		, ne60pg4	, ne120pg4
CAM-MPAS	      : mpasa480     , mpasa120


Variable resolution grids
=========================

ne0np4CONUS.ne30x8
ne0np4.ARCTIC.ne30x4
ne0np4.ARCTICGRIS.ne30x8

mpas_scrip_60-3_central_us
mpas_scrip_60-3_andes
mpas_scrip_60-15_sa


High -resolution that require special attention (i.e. near ~7-~3km)
